HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 311
By Stevens
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Shirley Maxine Winfree
of La Vergne.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Shirley Maxine Winfree, former mayor of La Vergne; and
WHEREAS, Shirley Winfree was an exemplary public servant and consummate
professional who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for her fellow citizens in
numerous capacities; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Winfree served with acumen and alacrity as the first female mayor of La
Vergne, winning election to the post in 1990; prior to her tenure as mayor, Ms. Winfree had
served her community as an alderman; and
WHEREAS, throughout her service as mayor, Shirley Winfree was instrumental in the
growth of La Vergne's population, and she helped create the La Vergne Water Treatment Plant,
which opened in 1993; and
WHEREAS, a trailblazer for women in her community, Shirley Winfree was the first
female business owner in Rutherford County, owning and operating Winfree Employment
Agency for many years; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Winfree was an active and devout member of Lavergne First Baptist
Church, which she served faithfully for many years; and
WHEREAS, deeply devoted to her family, Shirley Winfree always endeavored to remain
true to family values of the highest order; and
WHEREAS, she is survived by her granddaughter, Amber (Phillip) Davis; her grandson,
John Wesley Winfree; and her great-grandchildren, Skyla and Piper Davis, Haven Michelle
Winfree, and Wyatt Wesley Winfree; and
